title: For Sale:  Beware Scammer ANDREW BARNES
postcontent: This is a scam that's common on Craig's List and now has found its way here.  Someone offers to buy your item, often without fully understanding what it is.  They might even offer to pay more than you are asking because they want you to hold it for them or, in my case, a LOT more than I was asking because they want me to forward the extra money to someone else.  They then send you a BOGUS Cashier's Check.   This is typically simply a counterfeit from an obscure bank, but could be a real cashiers check that they then put a stop payment on.   You receive the check and ship the item.  They have your gun and you have a worthless piece of paper.
